Multi-bank support: connect more than one bank/card per person

Replaces the one-bank-per-user model with a per-bank `plaidConnections/{itemId}`
collection (server-only), keeping a legacy fallback so existing connections
keep working with no migration.

- exchangePublicToken: adds a connection (stores uid + institution name) instead
  of overwriting the user's single bank
- plaidWebhook: finds the connection by item_id (new collection, then legacy);
  tracks the sync cursor + reauth status per connection
- getAccounts: returns all connected banks, each with its masked accounts
- disconnectBank: disconnects ONE bank by itemId; updates bankStatus from what
  remains
- usePlaidConnect passes the institution name from Plaid Link
- BankAccounts: lists each bank (grouped) with a per-bank Disconnect; connect
  button now reads "Add a bank or card"
- firestore rules: plaidConnections is server-only

Tests: functions 59/59, frontend 103/103.

